        "section": "Prepare the reaction plate",
        "section_color": null,
        "section_duration": 0,
        "is_substep": false,
        "step": "Into each well of the plate, pipette\u00a02ul of normalized\u00a0gDNA sample (concentration of 20ng/ul) and 7.5ul of ultrapure water.\nBe sure to include wells for use as no template controls (no gDNA and 9.5ul of ultrapure water).\n\nUse a calibrated, positive-displacement pipettor to minimize contamination and error. Be sure that no cross-contamination occurs from well to well.\n ",
